**Summary of changes for pm-62p.3 (Agent multi-project scoping):**

- **`agents/project_manager/tools.py`** — Added `_PROJECT_ID` module-level variable, `set_project_id()` setter, and `_service()` factory. All 20+ tool functions now use `_service()` instead of `ProjectService()` directly.
- **`agents/project_manager/prompt.py`** — Converted to `build_system_prompt(project_name)` function. When a project name is provided, the prompt includes "You are managing the project: **{name}**".
- **`agents/project_manager/agent.py`** — Added `--project` CLI arg and `run(project_id)` function. Resolves project name from DB, scopes tools, prompt, journal check, and status snapshot.
- **`agents/reporter/agent.py`** — Added `--project` CLI arg. `run()` and `save_report()` accept `project_id`, scoping data loading and report output directory.
- **`agents/reporter/context.py`** — `load_all()` accepts optional `project_id` parameter.

All changes are backwards-compatible — omitting `--project` gives the original unscoped behavior.
